{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:galatians.5",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 5 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:1",
      "text": "For freedom Christ has set us free; stand fast therefore, and do not submit again to a yoke of slavery.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:2",
      "text": "Now I, Paul, say to you that if you receive circumcision, Christ will be of no advantage to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:3",
      "text": "I testify again to every man who receives circumcision that he is bound to keep the whole law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:4",
      "text": "You are severed from Christ, you who would be justified by the law; you have fallen away from grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:5",
      "text": "For through the Spirit, by faith, we wait for the hope of righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:6",
      "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision is of any avail, but faith working through love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:7",
      "text": "You were running well; who hindered you from obeying the truth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:8",
      "text": "This persuasion is not from him who calls you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:9",
      "text": "A little leaven leavens the whole lump.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:10",
      "text": "I have confidence in the Lord that you will take no other view than mine; and he who is troubling you will bear his judgment, whoever he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:11",
      "text": "But if I, brethren, still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? In that case the stumbling block of the cross has been removed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:12",
      "text": "I wish those who unsettle you would mutilate themselves!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:13",
      "text": "For you were called to freedom, brethren; only do not use your freedom as an opportunity for the flesh, but through love be servants of one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:14",
      "text": "For the whole law is fulfilled in one word, “You shall love your neighbor as yourself.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:15",
      "text": "But if you bite and devour one another take heed that you are not consumed by one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:16",
      "text": "But I say, walk by the Spirit, and do not gratify the desires of the flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:17",
      "text": "For the desires of the flesh are against the Spirit, and the desires of the Spirit are against the flesh; for these are opposed to each other, to prevent you from doing what you would.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:18",
      "text": "But if you are led by the Spirit you are not under the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:19",
      "text": "Now the works of the flesh are plain: fornication, impurity, licentiousness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:20",
      "text": "idolatry, sorcery, enmity, strife, jealousy, anger, selfishness, dissension, party spirit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:21",
      "text": "envy, drunkenness, carousing, and the like. I warn you, as I warned you before, that those who do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:22",
      "text": "But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:23",
      "text": "gentleness, self-control; against such there is no law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:24",
      "text": "And those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:25",
      "text": "If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.5.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:26",
      "text": "Let us have no self-conceit, no provoking of one another, no envy of one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
